[normal]) +
[normal] P 
[normal](Y
[normal] = Barriers ON /X = Barriers ON
[normal]) *P (X = Barriers 
[normal]ON
[normal])
[normal] 
[normal]= .9*.9+.1*.1= 
[normal]0.82. 
[normal]Now, 
[normal]P (Y= Barrier ON / X= Barrier ON)*P (X= Barrier ON) = .9*.9= .81
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Therefore, 
[normal]P(X = Barriers ON) / Y= Barriers ON
[normal]) = .81/.82= 98.7%.  Thus, our prior information Rate has been updated from 90% to 98.7%. 
