[normal]SIRI 2010 paper had drawn attention to this fact stating that other statutory bodies like Highways Authority or Local Councils and private individuals are involved in the matter and these interfaces 
[normal]need to be included in the Risk Equation. The UK Law Commission have published their recommendations to the Ministry of Transport in September 2013 to amend the law to allow duty of co-operation to be extended beyond the Infrastructure Manager and Railway 
[normal]Undertaking to other statutory authorities as well to facilitate faster closure of level crossings and bring all level crossings to be regulated by the UK Health and Safety at Work 1974 Act.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Third, if the UK Law Commission has recommended that the law
[normal] on level crossings be reformed in September 2013 to align with the UK HSE Best Practice for Risk Management, then how can the GB Industry claim that they were complaint with the law as the law as it applies t
[normal]o the level crossings itself found to be incons
[normal]istent and complex to apply? 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Fourth, t
[normal]he 
[normal]accident investigator 
[normal]and train driver account of the safety critical incident are not reliable
[normal] due to hindsight bias
[normal] in operation
[normal]. The observations of accident and train driver’s information 
[normal]cannot be included in
[normal] the Bayesian inference process as the random variable X is unobservable
[normal] in the risk analysis
[normal] (Kahneman, 2011)
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Thus, from Bayesian application to risk assessment(s), it is impo
[normal]rtant to recognise five
[normal] facts. First
[normal], it is possible to use two information i
[normal]tems through the Bayesian Rule to infer about the unobserved random variable. Two, reliability of the eye witness accounts must be known beforehand. 
[normal] 
[normal]Third, for truly random process, the probabilities
[normal] from relative frequency interpretation
[normal] cannot exceed 50
[normal]%. 
[normal] 
[normal]Fourth, we are not intuitive Bayesians. Fifth, we become 
[normal]Laplacians
[normal] due to operation of hindsight bias. 
