[normal]The
[normal] 
[normal]chances of
[normal] a train-bus collision increase with the following conditions
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The proximity of schools, farms, structure of roads leading to the AHB/ABCL and Unmanned Private Crossings afford chances of greater harm.  Apart from the long term measures of replacing lev
[normal]el crossings with suitable replacement like bridges etc, intermediate measures to safe-guard against loss of protection can be made. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]As reported by the Telegraph report in 2012
[normal], it is 
[normal]clear,
[normal] as ruled by the 
[normal]Magistrate, it
[normal] is better to mandate 
[normal]a clear 
[normal]vehicle 
[normal]space be afforded to the bus drivers
[normal] ( and others as well)
[normal] before they follow the traffic onto the crossing space. 
[normal] 
[normal]With this measure specified for the bus drivers, it is also mandatory that TPWS be installed at the stop signal to prevent a train e
[normal]ntering the crossing space when the barriers are raised. Modifications to the signalling systems and Highway Agency’s Rules and Regulations may be necessary as a result. 
[normal]Unwanted occurrences like increased costs of signalling projects, 
[normal] costs of civil engi
[normal]neering projects, 
[normal]waiting times at the level crossings, reduction in BTP police to monitor level crossings after a period 
[normal]etc are tasks for economists and lawyers to argue over and is beyond the data available to the author. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The idea that a vehicle stopp
[normal]ing ahead behind the level crossing barriers 
[normal]can be treated as a barrier 
[normal]advanced by Professor Stott’s Review 
[normal]does not accord
[normal] with the UK HSE Best Practice for Risk Management. This practice calls for designing safety into the system. 
[normal]Improving crash worth
[normal]iness of train vehicle from the collision with a vehicle on the level crossings may be appealing to few engineers and organisations
[normal]. But this method of 
[normal]passive barrier system is not so appealing if the crashing event can be prevented in first place by othe
[normal]r engineering measures. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In all the accident studies studied using the SIRI Methodology, author found that 
[normal]a stakeholder
[normal] in the form of s
[normal]uppliers, operator, and /or a researcher 
